net.hudup.logistic.math

Class BitAndNotProbItemMatrix

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.logistic.math.BitAndNotProbItemMatrix
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class BitAndNotProbItemMatrix
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class is matrix of AND and AND-NOT probabilities of binary items, in which each cell is a pair of AND probability and AND-NOT probability between two binary items. Such pair is called dual probability. This matrix is called binary dual probability matrix or bit dual probability matrix.
    Version:
    10.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen
    See Also:

    • Field Detail

      • bitItemMap

        protected java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,Pair> bitItemMap
        Items are translated into bit items. For example: item 1 with rating 4 is translated into 9. So each key (like 9) is the bit item id and each value is a pair of real item id (like 1) and real rating value (like 4).

      • matrix

        protected java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,BitAndNotProbItemMatrix.Prob>> matrix
        Main matrix of AND and AND-NOT probabilities of binary items. In other words, this is matrix of dual probabilities.

        public BitAndNotProbItemMatrix.Prob get(int bitRowId,
                                        int bitColId)
        Getting dual probability (AND and AND-NOT) at bit row ID and bit column ID. Note, both bit row ID and bit column ID are bit item id. Please call method contains(int, int) before calling this method. If method contains(int, int) returns false, the probability does not exist.
        Parameters:
        bitRowId - bit row ID.
        bitColId - bit column ID.
        Returns:
        dual probability (AND and AND-NOT) at bit row ID and bit column ID.
